To access the last element in a C# List, you can use the `Last()` method or index the List using the `Count` property.

Here is an example using both methods:

```csharp
List<int> numbers = new List<int>() { 1, 2, 3, 4, 5 };

// Method 1: Using Last() method
int lastElement1 = numbers.Last();

// Method 2: Using indexing with Count property
int lastElement2 = numbers[numbers.Count - 1];

Console.WriteLine("Last element using Last(): " + lastElement1);
Console.WriteLine("Last element using indexing: " + lastElement2);
```

Output:
```
Last element using Last(): 5
Last element using indexing: 5
```

Both methods will give you the same result, which is the value of the last element in the List.
